data: {"type": "text-delta", "id": "e38af64e-78e2-464e-baa4-ead9122ee482", "delta": "### Read-Only Checks for Disk Space Issues\n\nFor a Linux host running low on disk space, here are the **read-only commands** you should run first to diagnose the issue:\n\n#### 1. **Overall Disk Usage**\n```bash\ndf -h\n```\nShows mounted filesystems, total size, used space, available space, and usage percentage.\n\n#### 2. **Detailed Disk Usage by Directory**\n```bash\ndu -sh /* 2>/dev/null | sort -rh | head -20\n```\nLists the top 20 largest directories at the root level.\n\n#### 3. **Log Directory Analysis** (common culprit)\n```bash\ndu -sh /var/log/* 2>/dev/null | sort -rh | head -20\n```\nIdentifies large log files that may need rotation or cleanup.\n\n#### 4. **Find Large Files** (>100MB)\n```bash\nfind / -type f -size +100M -exec ls -lh {} \\; 2>/dev/null | head -30\n```\nLists files larger than 100MB across the filesystem.\n\n#### 5. **Check for Deleted but Open Files**\n```bash\nlsof +L1 2>/dev/null | head -20\n```\nShows files that are deleted but still held open by processes (common cause of \"ghost\" disk usage).\n\n#### 6. **Inode Usage**\n```bash\ndf -i\n```\nChecks if you're running out of inodes (file count limit) rather than space.\n\n#### 7. **Recent Large Files** (modified in last 7 days)\n```bash\nfind / -type f -mtime -7 -size +50M -exec ls -lh {} \\; 2>/dev/null | head -20\n```\nIdentifies recently modified large files.\n\n#### 8. **Check for Core Dumps**\n```bash\nfind /var /tmp /home -name \"core*\" -o -name \"*.core\" -o -name \"core.*\" 2>/dev/null | head -20\n```\nCore dump files can consume significant space.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Action Available\nI can also run the **Disk Usage Report** service from the catalog, which executes:\n```bash\ndf -h && du -sh /var/log/* 2>/dev/null | sort -rh | head -20\n```\n\n**Do you want me to run this on a specific host?** Just provide the hostname or IP, and I'll execute it immediately (no approval required)."}

